    "message_1": "A retailer wants to predict their monthly sales based on the average temperature in their area. They collected data for the last 12 months and found that the average monthly temperature and sales (in thousands of dollars) are:\n\n| Temperature | Sales |\n|-------------|-------|\n| 65          | 45    |\n| 70          | 50    |\n| 75          | 55    |\n| 80          | 60    |\n| 85          | 70    |\n| 90          | 75    |\n| 95          | 85    |\n| 100         | 90    |\n| 105         | 95    |\n| 110         | 100   |\n| 115         | 110   |\n| 120         | 115   |\n\nUsing linear regression analysis, what is the predicted sales for the retailer when the temperature is 100 degrees Fahrenheit?",
    "message_2": "To predict the sales using linear regression, we first need to find the equation of the line of best fit. The equation of a line is given by y = mx + b, where m is the slope and b is the y-intercept.\n\n1. Calculate the mean of the temperatures (x) and the mean of the sales (y):\n\nMean of temperatures (x̄) = (65 + 70 + 75 + 80 + 85 + 90 + 95 + 100 + 105 + 110 + 115 + 120) / 12 = 1035 / 12 = 86.25\n\nMean of sales (ȳ) = (45 + 50 + 55 + 60 + 70 + 75 + 85 + 90 + 95 + 100 + 110 + 115) / 12 = 950 / 12 = 79.17\n\n2. Calculate the slope (m):\n\nm = Σ[(xi - x̄)(yi - ȳ)] / Σ(xi - x̄)^2\n\nFor each data point, calculate (xi - x̄)(yi - ȳ) and (xi - x̄)^2:\n\n| Temperature | Sales | (xi - x̄) | (yi - ȳ) | (xi - x̄)(yi - ȳ) | (xi - x̄)^2 |\n|-------------|-------|----------|----------|-----------------|------------|\n| 65          | 45    | -21.25   | -34.17   | 726.04           | 451.56      |\n| 70          | 50    | -16.25   | -29.17   | 473.96           | 264.06      |\n| 75          | 55    | -11.25   | -24.17   | 272.29           | 126.56      |\n| 80          | 60    | -6.25    | -19.17   | 119.79           | 39.06       |\n| 85          | 70    | -1.25    | -9.17    | 11.46            | 1.56        |\n| 90          | 75    | 3.75     | -4.17    | -15.63           | 14.06       |\n| 95          | 85    | 8.75     | 5.83     | 51.04            | 76.56       |\n| 100         | 90    | 13.75    | 10.83    | 149.04           | 189.06      |\n| 105         | 95    | 18.75    | 15.83    | 297.29           | 351.56      |\n| 110         | 100   | 23.75    | 20.83    | 494.79           | 564.06      |\n| 115         | 110   | 28.75    | 30.83    | 886.46           | 826.56      |\n| 120         | 115   | 33.75    | 35.83    | 1209.79          | 1139.06     |\n\nΣ(xi - x̄)(yi - ȳ) = 3674.53\nΣ(xi - x̄)^2 = 3914.16\n\nm = 3674.53 / 3914.16 = 0.939\n\n3. Calculate the y-intercept (b):\n\nb = ȳ - m * x̄ = 79.17 - 0.939 * 86.25 = 79.17 - 80.96 = -1.79\n\n4. The equation of the line of best fit is:\n\ny = 0.939x - 1.79\n\n5. Predict the sales when the temperature is 100 degrees Fahrenheit:\n\ny = 0.939 * 100 - 1.79 = 93.9 - 1.79 = 92.11\n\nThe predicted sales for the retailer when the temperature is 100 degrees Fahrenheit is approximately $92,110."
